From 9a84dd62158741241deddc147f1a22214ae9f56e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Paul Meyer <katexochen0@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Apr 2026 16:25:52 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Skip default_permissions in multi-user mode

In multi-user mode with allow_other, the kernel FUSE module gates
access via fuse_allow_current_process() which checks allow_other and
verifies the caller is in the same user namespace or a descendant.

Remove default_permissions in multi-user mode: this kernel-level DAC
check uses capable_wrt_inode_uidgid() which verifies CAP_DAC_OVERRIDE
in the FUSE mount's user namespace. Callers in a child user namespace
(e.g. Nix sandbox) lack capabilities in the host namespace, causing
EACCES for operations that would succeed on a regular FS.

Without default_permissions, the FUSE daemon's own backing-FS access
(via Guard::drop_privileges) still enforces per-file authorization.

Amp-Thread-ID: https://ampcode.com/threads/T-019d916b-f8b6-745a-8c11-6768858e16ce
Co-authored-by: Amp <amp@ampcode.com>

Signed-off-by: Paul Meyer <katexochen0@gmail.com>
---
 disorderfs.cpp | 6 ++++--
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/disorderfs.cpp b/disorderfs.cpp
index d2c4eda..e9edb6d 100644
--- a/disorderfs.cpp
+++ b/disorderfs.cpp
@@ -268,8 +268,10 @@ int        main (int argc, char** argv)
     }
 
     // Add some of our own hard-coded FUSE options:
-    fuse_opt_add_arg(&fargs, "-o");
-    fuse_opt_add_arg(&fargs, "default_permissions"); // XXX: other mount options?
+    if (!config.multi_user) {
+        fuse_opt_add_arg(&fargs, "-o");
+        fuse_opt_add_arg(&fargs, "default_permissions");
+    }
     if (config.multi_user) {
         fuse_opt_add_arg(&fargs, "-o");
         fuse_opt_add_arg(&fargs, "allow_other");
-- 
